sourcePackage.description: This VIB contains all of the base functionality of vSphere ESXi.

optionDef.label: Welcome message for the Direct Console User Interface (DCUI)
optionDef.summary: A welcome message in the initial screen of the Direct Console User Interface (DCUI). Use an empty string to reset to the default message.

optionDef.label: Enable
optionDef.summary: Enable Content Based Read Cache

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.mode.d.eax
optionDef.summary: Controls the use of Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.val.d.eax; legal values "mask", "clobber", or "disable".

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.mode.d.ebx
optionDef.summary: Controls the use of Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.val.d.ebx; legal values "mask", "clobber", or "disable".

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.mode.d.ecx
optionDef.summary: Controls the use of Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.val.d.ecx; legal values "mask", "clobber", or "disable".

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.mode.d.edx
optionDef.summary: Controls the use of Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.val.d.edx; legal values "mask", "clobber", or "disable".

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.val.d.eax
optionDef.summary: CPUID override that may be applied to level d register eax; controlled by Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.mode.d.eax.

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.val.d.ebx
optionDef.summary: CPUID override that may be applied to level d register ebx; controlled by Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.mode.d.ebx.

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.val.d.ecx
optionDef.summary: CPUID override that may be applied to level d register ecx; controlled by Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.mode.d.ecx.

optionDef.label: cpuidMask.val.d.edx
optionDef.summary: CPUID override that may be applied to level d register edx; controlled by Config.Defaults.cpuidMask.mode.d.edx.

optionDef.label: HostLocalSwapDirEnabled
optionDef.summary: Enable use of host-local swap directory

optionDef.label: VMOverheadGrowthLimit
optionDef.summary: Default limit (in MB) on VM overhead memory growth. Valid values are 0 to maximum memory supported, and 0xffffffff which means "unlimited".

optionDef.label: Enabled
optionDef.summary: Enable hot migration support

optionDef.label: Vmknic
optionDef.summary: vmknic for vMotion vmkernel VNIC

optionDef.label: DefaultHardwareVersion
optionDef.summary: Default virtual machine compatibility

optionDef.label: vsanWitnessVirtualAppliance
optionDef.summary: Indicates a vSAN witness host running in a Virtual Appliance. VM services (create/register/power on) are blocked

optionDef.label: Syslog.global.defaultRotate
optionDef.summary: Default number of rotated logs to keep. Reset to default on zero.

optionDef.label: Syslog.global.defaultSize
optionDef.summary: Default size of logs before rotation, in KiB. Reset to default on zero.

optionDef.label: Syslog.global.logDir
optionDef.summary: Datastore path of directory to output logs to. Reset to default on null. Example: [datastoreName]/logdir

optionDef.label: Syslog.global.logDirUnique
optionDef.summary: Place logs in a unique subdirectory of logdir, based on hostname.

optionDef.label: Syslog.global.logHost
optionDef.summary: The remote host to output logs to. Reset to default on null. Multiple hosts are supported and must be separated with comma (,). Example: udp://hostName1:514, hostName2, ssl://hostName3:1514

optionDef.label: Logger rotations
optionDef.summary: Number of rotated logs to keep for this logger. Reset to default on zero.

optionDef.label: Logger size
optionDef.summary: Set size of logs before rotation for this logger, in KiB. Reset to default on zero.

optionDef.label: Logger rotations
optionDef.summary: Number of rotated logs to keep for this logger. Reset to default on zero.

optionDef.label: Logger size
optionDef.summary: Set size of logs before rotation for this logger, in KiB. Reset to default on zero.

optionDef.label: SuppressCoredumpWarning
optionDef.summary: Do not show warning for disabled or unconfigured coredump target

optionDef.label: SuppressShellWarning
optionDef.summary: Do not show warning for enabled local and remote shell access

optionDef.label: Log level
optionDef.summary: vCenter agent logging level
